


01-31-2023 - Variables & String


DataType  variableName  = value;
int age = 25;

Naming rules:

Unwritten rules:
1. CamelCase
2. Meaningful name
3. Variable name should not start with a capital letter

Written Rules:
1. No Spaces
2. Digits are allowed except in the beginning of the variable name
3. _ and $ are allowed to be used anywhere in the Variable name





int age;					-> true
byte AGE;					-> False
short shift$;				-> True
byte number of students;	-> False
char _firstLetter;			-> true
int 8students;				-> False
boolean isWheatherSnowing#; -> False
double @balance;			-> False





boolean b1, b2;			->True
int i1 = 45, i2;		->True
double d1, double d2;	->False
byte b1; byte b2;		->True but unorganized
int i3; i4;				->False












